<br>
* a Legends loophole to import top-end gear from other servers<br>
* lack of NO DROP tags on FV<br>
* the recent patch fixing the Bazaar to allow sale of these items<br>
<br>
it is inevitable that the Ebayers will swarm to FV like rats to a smelly hunk of cheese. It is appalling. There is NO reason they should allow character transfers with gear intact to FV with the possible exception of FV-originated characters returning from Legends -- and then ONLY with gear they brought from FV. Anything else is just too ripe for abuse given the no NO DROP rule here.<br>
<br>
I really, really want to hear VI's reasoning for allowing unstripped transfers from Legends to FV. Maybe they are really concerned about revenue and nothing more, and the cash paid by Ebayers buying Legends subscriptions for the express purpose of importing NO DROP gear to FV, trading it for big plat, then selling the plat for real cash is enough to make them look the other way. Hell, the loophole works both ways I bet. Import top-end gear to FV where it can be traded for plat, then transfer the plat back to another server where it'll fetch a higher price on playerauctions. It is positively sickening.<br>
<br>
I do understand the attractiveness of FV to powergamers who want to play the top-end game unfettered by NO DROP rules. That is a very, very nice change from other servers where great gear has to rot or be destroyed regularly. I don't have any problem with folks who come here for that reason, as long as they play by the rules, aren't disrespectful to roleplayers in-game, and don't sell their stuff for real life cash. I don't see why anyone should get upset about that.<br>
<br>
But allowing high-end characters to come over with gear intact just opens up this huge loophole that we have seen. This loophole needs to be closed, now.<br>
<br>
